article.description: No. 2 Texas came away with a victory Sunday, beating North Carolina State 69-56 in the Jimmy V Classic.
article.headline: Texas finds way to put away N.C. State
article.linkText: Locked in: No. 2 Longhorns put away Wolfpack
article.story:
RALEIGH, N.C. (AP) -- Texas coach Judy Conradt saw this coming.

"It was exactly what I thought it would be -- ugly at times,"
Conradt said. "I thought we'd be lucky to get out of here with a win.
We weren't exactly a well-oiled machine."

Still, the No. 2 Longhorns came away with a victory Sunday,
beating North Carolina State 69-56 in the Jimmy V Classic.

Texas shot better than the Wolfpack and outrebounded them. But
Conradt saw another side to the game -- 18 Texas turnovers compared
with the Wolfpack's 22; 20 personal fouls to the Wolfpack's 12.

Texas (2-0) got its second straight win against an Atlantic
Coast Conference school. The Longhorns beat then-No. 2 Duke on Nov.
16 in the opener for both teams.

Texas junior transfer Jamie Carey hit seven straight shots in
the second half and finished with 23 points, her most as a
Longhorn.

"Coach said they were going to pressure us along the outside,
so we needed to penetrate," Carey said. "My teammates were able
to get me the ball when I needed it and I was able to do that."

Texas got 14 points from Kala Bowers and 11 rebounds out of
Tiffany Jackson. Nina Norman added nine points and seven assists.

North Carolina State (1-1) was led by Kaayla Chones' 19 points
and 11 boards.

"We knew they were going to come out tough in the second half,
so we just had to take it to them on offense and defense like they
took it to us," Chones said.

The Wolfpack hit four of their first five shots of the second
half and trailed 45-39 with 12:45 to play. Texas went on an 8-2
run, keyed by four points from Carey, and N.C. State didn't get
closer than 10 points.

"When they needed her [Carey], she was there," N.C. State coach Kay Yow said. "She just took over."
